Currently when JIRA software is integrated with Google account the JIRA username must match the first part of the email (before @) in order to use Google authentication. I believe it would be much more convenient if the matching was done basing on the email set in the JIRA profile. This way adding Google integration or changing to another one would be easier, as currently if the usernames do not match emails the recommendation is to create new users, which cause a lot of issues (loosing history, dashboards etc).

Proposed solutin:

Google authentication should match users basing on the email instead of username

