I'd like to be able to put a project in shadow maintenance mode when the environment is experiencing a major problem.  This would allow QA to keep entering tickets for the rampant bugs all over the busted up product allowing them to feel useful while they ignore the emails and chats about the product having global problems.  

Once the system was fixed and the project was removed from this mode, no trace of all the bugs entered would exist.

